<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B10FF8FFF6CFDD3FC8ADA0D" blockId="34.[192,884,515,539]" box="[192,884,515,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFDD3FE84DA0D" bold="true" box="[192,378,515,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B10FF8FFF6CFDD3FEFBDA0D" box="[192,261,515,539]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Raton Mesa, Colfax County, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B10FF8FFD75FDD4FC8EDA0D" box="[729,880,515,539]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B10FF8FFF6CFD93FAD2DA6D" blockId="34.[192,1440,579,635]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFD93FE6BDA4D" bold="true" box="[192,405,579,603]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Type label data.</emphasis>
I have not examined the label data associated with this specimen. Scott (1981) includes the following data: “ 
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B10FF8FFE1FFDB3FDDBDA6D" box="[435,549,611,635]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Holotype</typeStatus>
, male, Raton Mesa, Colfax Co. New Mex. 
<date id="FFEB10107B10FF8FFBB4FDB3FB4BDA6D" box="[1048,1205,611,635]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" value="1972-07-21">21 July 1972</date>
, J. Scott”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B10FF8FFF6CFD73FC42DAED" blockId="34.[192,1440,675,764]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFD73FD19DAAD" bold="true" box="[192,743,675,699]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Considered one of the palest 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFBE4FD74FACADAAD" box="[1096,1332,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFBE4FD74FB39DAAD" box="[1096,1223,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantis">S. atlantis</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFB7CFD73FACADAAD" box="[1232,1332,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesperis">hesperis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
forms, it is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFEFBFD14FD8EDACD" authorityName="Moeck" authorityYear="1950" box="[343,624,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="greyi">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFEFBFD14FD8EDACD" box="[343,624,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis greyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B10FF8FFD39FD13FD06DACD" box="[661,760,707,731]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFCADFD14FBA3DACD" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1981" box="[769,1117,707,731]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="ratonensis">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFCADFD14FBA3DACD" box="[769,1117,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis ratonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always has silver spots on the ventral hindwings. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity id="4CAD9B357B10FF8FFC97FD33FC46DAED" box="[827,952,739,763]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="52.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="50.0">50-55 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B10FF8FFF6CFCF3FC63DB2D" blockId="34.[192,925,803,827]" box="[192,925,803,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFCF3FEE1DB2D" bold="true" box="[192,287,803,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Range.</emphasis>
Limited to Raton Mesa in northeastern 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B10FF8FFCAEFCF4FC67DB2D" box="[770,921,803,827]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B10FF8FFF6CFCB3FDB6DBCD" blockId="34.[192,1441,867,987]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFCB3FE92DB6D" bold="true" box="[192,364,867,891]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Life history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFED8FCB4FD2BDB6D" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1981" box="[372,725,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="ratonensis">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFED8FCB4FD2BDB6D" box="[372,725,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Speyeria hesperis ratonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be a Pleistocene relict related to prairie dwelling 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFA2BFCB4FE86DB8D" authorityName="dos Passos and Grey" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="helena">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFA2BFCB4FE86DB8D" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. hesperis helena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F34276407B10FF8FFE37FC53FE04DB8D" box="[411,506,899,923]" name="Canada" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Canada</collectingCountry>
(Scott 1981). The two populations likely inhabited mixed grassland and aspen forests on the southern plains. When the climate warmed, 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFC00FC74FC20DBAD" box="[940,990,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. h</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B10FF8FFC5CFC73FBBFDBAD" box="[1008,1089,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helena">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFC5CFC73FBBFDBAD" box="[1008,1089,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">helena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
advanced north while 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFAC9FC74FA66DBAD" box="[1381,1432,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">S. h</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B10FF8FFF6CFC14FEC1DBCD" box="[192,319,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">ratonensis</emphasis>
move up in elevation.
</paragraph>
